          },
          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Nickel and copper foils as monitors for cyclotron",
                "beam intensities"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "G.A.Brinkman",
                "J.Helmer",
                "L.Lindner"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "2NEDAMS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,RRL,28,9,1977",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,RRL,28,9,1977",
                    "doi": null,
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "RRL",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "28",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "9"
                      },
                      "date": 1977
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SYNCY"
                ],
                "institute": "2NEDIKO"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Irradiations were performed in the",
                " extracted beam (diam.= 2 cm)",
                "target foils of diam. = 3 cm. Beam intensities were",
                "in the order of tens to hundreds of nanoamperes."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The nickel and copper foils used consisted of high",
                "purity metal of natural isotopic composition with",
                "thicknesses of 94 mg Ni/cm2 (58Ni -68.3%; 60Ni -26.1%,",
                "61Ni - 1.1%) and 8.7 mg Cu/cm2 (65Cu - 30.9%),",
                "respectively. Degradation of beam energy in these",
                "foils was calculated using tabulated data from",
                "C.F.Williamson, etc., Tables of range and stopping",
                "power, Saclay, CEA-R-3042,1966."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma-ray measurements were performed using",
                "a 10% (relative to a 3 in. x 3 in. Nal(Tl) detector)",
                "Ge(Li) solid state detector, ca1ibrated with a set of",
                "standard sources."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Monitor foils were placed in a vacuum chamber provided",
                "with a target array to select one out of several target",
                "foils for insertion in the beam. Beam intensities were",
                "calibrated directly by using a conventional Faraday",
                "cup. This was done immediately before and after",
                "activation, with the target-foils withdrawn from the",
                "beam. During irradiation of the foils beam currents",
                "were held constant within a few percent."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Additional cross section for 100% isotopic abundance",
                "for the following reactions listed in Table 1:",
                "    58Ni(d,x)57Ni : 111 mb at 50.6 MeV",
                "    58Ni(p,x)55Co : 57 mb  at 50.6 MeV",
                "    65Cu(p,x)64Cu : 184 mb at 51.0 MeV",
                "    63Cu(p,x)58Co : 161 mb at 51.0 Mev"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
